main event: Four witnesses observed an unknown object in the sky over Anaheim, California on July 28, 1955 at around 10:55 pm.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 6 minutes.
The object was described as having a brightness similar to an ordinary star and appearing illuminated in various colors including red, green, white, and blue.
The object moved out of sight towards the northwest.
The investigator's notes indicate this appears to be an unidentified aerial phenomenon, as the observed flight characteristics cannot be explained by any known aircraft or celestial object.
The report includes a technical information questionnaire that the witness filled out to provide additional details about the sighting.
sighted object: An unknown, bright, illuminated object in the sky
